docker.io (28.5.1-2) trixie; urgency=medium

  * BREAKING: Split into modular packages following Debian best practices
  * New package structure:
    - docker.io: Docker Engine daemon (dockerd, docker-proxy)
    - containerd: Container runtime (containerd, containerd-shim-runc-v2)
    - runc: OCI runtime (runc)
  * docker.io now depends on containerd and runc packages
  * Each package has its own systemd service files
  * Smoother upgrade path from separate containerd/runc installations
  * Better modularity: install containerd without Docker if needed

 -- Bruno Verachten <gounthar@gmail.com>  Sat, 18 Oct 2025 17:50:00 +0200

docker.io (28.5.1-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release Docker v28.5.1
  * Package renamed from docker-engine-riscv64 to docker.io (standard name)
  * Complete runtime stack included:
    - dockerd (Docker Engine daemon v28.5.1)
    - docker-proxy (network proxy)
    - containerd v1.7.28 (container runtime)
    - runc v1.3.0 (OCI runtime)
    - containerd-shim-runc-v2 (containerd shim)
  * Built from official moby v28.5.1 release
  * Built on Debian Trixie with Go 1.25.3
  * Native RISC-V64 compilation on BananaPi F3
  * Designed for APT repository deployment

 -- Bruno Verachten <gounthar@gmail.com>  Fri, 18 Oct 2025 14:30:00 +0200

docker-engine-riscv64 (1.0.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package release for RISC-V64
  * Built from Moby commit 83264918d3
  * Includes dockerd (Docker Engine daemon)
  * Includes docker-proxy (network proxy)
  * Built on Debian Trixie with Go 1.25.3
  * Native RISC-V64 compilation on BananaPi F3

